editorialSummary.text: Cozy neighborhood standby where Southwestern cuisine is accompanied by potent margaritas.

originalText.text:
I recently dined at this outstanding Mexican restaurant in NYC, and I can't stop raving about it! From the moment I walked in, I was greeted with warm hospitality and an inviting ambiance. The menu offered a tantalizing array of authentic Mexican dishes that left my taste buds dancing with delight.

I got the enchiladas, which were a true masterpiece. Filled with tender, perfectly seasoned meat and smothered in a rich, flavorful sauce, each bite was a burst of deliciousness.

The margaritas were expertly crafted, striking the ideal balance of sweetness and tang, and they paired beautifully with my meal. The staff was attentive, knowledgeable, and clearly passionate about the cuisine.

If you're in NYC and craving an unforgettable Mexican dining experience, this restaurant is a must-visit!!!!

originalText.text: What a decline!  I've been going to this wonderful family owned restaurant for 15 years.  Pandemic losses forced the 3rd generation of owners to co-sign with the landlord to survive.  The day after Thanksgiving 2022 the landlord FIRED the family owners for no other reason than to take advantage of post-pandemic recovery and force the steal of their business.  But they have (had) the best burger and fries in town!  So 3 times now I have (guiltily) ordered it, delivery, as before.  The fries are now mysteriously soggy, the burger is always overdone, and NO attention is paid to requests as simple as 'onion on the side, please', even though that used to be standard.  It's just gone.  Not an option.  Even when one asks nicely.  I finally have to accept that Santa Fe has gone from an UWS delicious and welcoming haven to shockingly mediocre.  ðŸ˜¥

originalText.text: The food was fine, large portions. The fish was crispy and everything was enjoyable, but not particularly memorable. It didn't taste particularly like freaky made food. The staff was attentive but a bit distracted, even on a mostly empty house they forgot part of the order and brought the wrong check.

originalText.text: The guacamole was good. ($15 for a small dish of it.) The water was cold. The table was available immediately, compared to a 30 minute wait where we tried to go first. The food truly was not very good. We ordered chicken fajitas and the chicken was so gross and chewy I had to spit it out in my napkin.  The tortillas were obviously from a plastic package and smelled and tasted as such. The chips tasted like they came from a cheap grocery store bag. We didn't care for the salsa. Overall, we would Definitely not return. We were tired and just wanted to leave without a fuss but our food was pretty gross,in particular the chicken fajitas. We are used to fresh salsas, chips and tortillas so it was a real disappointment.  The atmosphere outside was nice on a pleasant fall evening and the staff was polite.
